
Definition:
Operators are special symbols used to perform
operations on variables and values.

Example:
+, -, *, /, ==, and, or

Operands:
Values on which operators are applied.


# 🔹 1. Arithmetic Operators

```python
# Arithmetic operators perform mathematical operations

a = 15
b = 4

print("Addition:", a + b)
print("Subtraction:", a - b)
print("Multiplication:", a * b)
print("Division:", a / b)
print("Floor Division:", a // b)
print("Modulus:", a % b)
print("Exponentiation:", a ** b)
```

---

## ✅ Output

```python
Addition: 19
Subtraction: 11
Multiplication: 60
Division: 3.75
Floor Division: 3
Modulus: 3
Exponentiation: 50625
```

---

## 📌 Important Arithmetic Operators

| Operator | Meaning        |
| -------- | -------------- |
| +        | Addition       |
| -        | Subtraction    |
| *        | Multiplication |
| /        | Division       |
| //       | Floor Division |
| %        | Modulus        |
| **       | Power          |

---

