# 🔹 3. Logical Operators

```python
# Logical operators combine conditions

a = True
b = False

print(a and b)
print(a or b)
print(not a)
```

---

## ✅ Output

```python
False
True
False
```

---

## 📌 Logical Operators

| Operator | Meaning              |
| -------- | -------------------- |
| and      | Both conditions true |
| or       | At least one true    |
| not      | Reverse condition    |

---

## 🎯 Interview Questions

* Difference between `and` and `or`
* What is short-circuit evaluation?(Short-circuit evaluation is a programming concept where a condition stops evaluating as soon as the final result is already known.)

