# 🔹 4. Bitwise Operators

```python
# Bitwise operators work on binary bits

a = 10
b = 4

print(a & b)
print(a | b)
print(~a)
print(a ^ b)
print(a >> 2)
print(a << 2)
```

---

## ✅ Output

```python
0
14
-11
14
2
40
```

---

## 📌 Bitwise Operators

| Operator | Meaning     |
| -------- | ----------- |
| &        | AND         |
| |        | OR          |
| ^        | XOR         |
| ~        | NOT         |
| >>       | Right Shift |
| <<       | Left Shift  |

---

## 🎯 Interview Questions

* What is XOR?
* Difference between logical and bitwise operators?

